Renew Policy Business Process
When it's time to renew your policy, you get an email with a renewal link. Enter some details for the renewal and it's all done.

Renew Policy OmniScript
The Renew Policy workflow renews your policy.
It takes a policy Id and uses services to retrieve data about vehicles insured by this policy and corresponding coverages for them.
It displays vehicle and coverage details, lets users modify coverages, reprices policy accordingly, and updates price on user interface.
A Data Mapper updates the old policy to show that it has been renewed.
The OmniScript then uses a FlexCard to show information about the renewed policy.

What's in the Renew Policy OmniScript
It has components to get insured items and policy coverages, set renewal dates and policy ID, configure coverages, and update policies.

SetPolicyId - Retrieves effective date and policy ID of the policy.
GetInsuredItems - Calls service to get list of insured items.
GetPolicyCoverages - Calls service to get list of applicable coverages.
setDisplayValues - Transforms policy data for display.
SetRenewDate - Retrieves policy renewal date.
configure - Lets users configure coverages for renewed policy.
createUpdatePolicy - Creates the renewed policy using integration procedure.
UpdateOldPolicy - Updates old policy record renewal information.

How to Renew a Policy
Customer services reps, policyholders and brokers can renew policies three different ways:
